---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'DGS Certified Cleaning Services for Government Facilities';
const description = 'DGS certified commercial cleaning for state and government facilities in the San Joaquin Valley. Learn about DGS certification, state cleaning standards, and how System4 serves government facilities with Cert. ID 2022081.';
const pubDate = '2026-07-10';
const author = 'System4 San Joaquin Valley';
const slug = 'dgs-certified-cleaning-services';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="blog-post" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Article">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": title,
      "description": description,
      "datePublished": pubDate,
      "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "System4 San Joaquin Valley" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "System4 San Joaquin Valley", "url": "https://system4sjv.com" },
      "url": `https://system4sjv.com/blog/${slug}/`
    })} />

    <section class="hero hero-compact" data-animate>
      <div class="container hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-content">
          <div class="hero-tag">Blog</div>
          <h1>{title}</h1>
          <p class="hero-sub">{description}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container" style="max-width:760px;">

        <p>If you manage a state, county, or local government facility in the San Joaquin Valley, finding a qualified cleaning contractor that meets DGS standards can be a challenge. Government facilities have unique requirements — from security protocols to documentation standards — that most commercial cleaning companies aren't equipped to handle.</p>

        <p>This guide explains what DGS certified cleaning services are, how state certification works, and what government facility managers should look for in a cleaning partner.</p>

        <h2>What Is DGS Certification?</h2>
        <p>The <strong>Department of General Services (DGS)</strong> oversees procurement for the State of California. DGS certification verifies that a business meets specific standards for working with state and local government agencies.</p>
        <p>For cleaning services, DGS certification means:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Pre-vetted vendor:</strong> The cleaning company has been reviewed for financial stability, past performance, and compliance</li>
          <li><strong>Competitive pricing:</strong> State-negotiated rates ensure fair pricing for government clients</li>
          <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> The vendor meets all state requirements for insurance, bonding, and worker safety</li>
          <li><strong>Simplified procurement:</strong> Government agencies can contract directly without a lengthy bidding process</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>System4's DGS Certification</h2>
        <p>System4 holds <strong>DGS Certification ID 2022081</strong> for janitorial and custodial services. This means state and local agencies in the San Joaquin Valley can procure cleaning services from System4 through a streamlined process, with pricing and terms already established.</p>
        <p>Our DGS certification covers a comprehensive range of cleaning services for government facilities, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Daily janitorial and custodial services</li>
          <li>Floor care (strip & wax, scrub & recoat)</li>
          <li>Carpet cleaning and deep extraction</li>
          <li>Window washing (interior and exterior)</li>
          <li>Disinfection and sanitization services</li>
          <li>Post-construction cleanup</li>
          <li>Day porter services</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cleaning Standards for Government Facilities</h2>
        <p>Government facilities are held to high cleanliness standards. State requirements set specific expectations for:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Restroom sanitation frequency and quality</li>
          <li>Common area cleaning schedules</li>
          <li>Safety data sheet (SDS) compliance and green cleaning mandates</li>
          <li>ADA compliance for accessible cleaning</li>
          <li>Background-checked and uniformed personnel</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why Choose a DGS Certified Vendor</h2>
        <p>For government facility managers, choosing a DGS certified vendor offers several advantages:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Simplified procurement:</strong> No lengthy competitive bidding process required</li>
          <li><strong>Accountability:</strong> DGS certified vendors are subject to ongoing performance reviews</li>
          <li><strong>Compliance assurance:</strong> All insurance, bonding, and safety requirements are pre-verified</li>
          <li><strong>Local presence:</strong> System4 serves the entire San Joaquin Valley with dedicated territory managers</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Get Started</h2>
        <p>If you manage a government facility in Stockton, Modesto, Tracy, Manteca, Lodi, or Turlock, here's how to start:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Contact System4 for a free facility walkthrough and assessment</li>
          <li>Review our DGS certification (ID 2022081) to confirm scope and pricing</li>
          <li>Schedule a site visit to customize a cleaning plan for your facility</li>
          <li>Begin service with no long-term contract required</li>
        </ol>

        <p>With <strong>20+ years of experience</strong>, <strong>67+ locations nationwide</strong>, and DGS certification, System4 of San Joaquin Valley is the trusted choice for government facility cleaning in the Central Valley.</p>

        <p style="margin-top:2rem;"><a href="/services/" style="color:var(--blue);font-weight:600;">Explore our commercial cleaning services →</a></p>

      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Layout>